malnutrition in patients undergoing gastroenterological and hernia surgery: an analysis of 374 patients
Participants 133 454 6
The aim of this study was to assess the nutritional status of 374 surgical patients with gastrointestinal disease and hernias of the abdominal wall; to identify risk factors associated with a poorer nutritional status in this group of patients and to assess awareness of the patient's nutritional status by medical teams.
Participants 989 1204 6
The 374 patients evaluated in this study were a subgroup of a larger multicenter, cross-sectional, randomized study that was carried out in 1996. Nutritional status was assessed by using Subjective Global Assessment
